page.title: 17Wildlife
page.content: Around where I live, you get a lot of wildlife. There are a lot of{swallows, {martins}and{swifts.}At the moment there is a{kestrel}around, I have seen it 3 times. In the fields behind my friend's house we spotted a{water {vole.}On the pond where I saw the vole there are also{mallards,pochards}and { {canada geese.}When my friend and I went to the ponds again we found a young{rabbit.}We thought it would run away but it didn't, so we picked it up and stroked it.After a bit it jumped out of my arms and ran off. At Cadeby, when I went fishing I saw this swallow diving on the water catching flies. When I was down the strawberry fields I spotted a pair of{yellow wagtails. } I have seen quite a lot of rare birds where I live and my favourite is the kestrel. By Jamie Pinder, aged 10.
